  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The model is intended to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A full 13-factor assessment was performed: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The intended use scope — adult CPB flow rates 3–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, 37 °C blood analogue — is documented in the Claim and Requirement nodes referenced below. Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
